title.rendered: TNPL 2022: CSG vs NRK, 1st Match, Playing XI, Match Prediction,  Venue, Pitch report, Head-To-Head all details

content.rendered:
The sixth season of the Tamil Nadu Premier League (TNPL), which will start tomorrow, June 23, and end on July 31, is about to get underway. Eights teams will compete against one another in a round-robin style, similar to that of other leagues.

The highly anticipated sixth season of the Tamil Nadu Premier League will go off with Chepauk Super Gillies vs Nellai Royal Kings in the opening game tomorrow (2022). , let’s get into the specifics of the match, such as how it will be broadcast, streamed, where it will be played, when it will be played, etc.

CSG vs NRK Playing squad

Chepauk Super Gillies

S Radhakrishnan, Kaushik Gandhi (captain), Uthirasamy Sasidev, N Jagadeesan (wk), Ravisrinivasan, Sai Kishore, Rajagopal Sathish, Harish Kumar, B Arun, Manimaran Siddharth, Sonu Yadav, S Sujay, Arun Kumar, R Alexander, Arun Kumar, Jaganath Srinivas, Sandeep Warrier, Nilesh Subramanian, Dev Rahul, Sai Prakash, V Santhanasekar, S Vijay Kumar, H Prashid Akash

Nellai Royal Kings

Trilok Nag H, Harish N S, Aparajith B, Sanjay Yadav R, Pradosh Ranjan Paul, Indrajith B, V Athisayaraj Davidson, Senthil Nathan S, Jitendra Murthy, Arjun P Murthy, Jitendra Kumar CH, Sarath Kumar M, Sharun Kumar S, Rohit Ram R, Veeramani T, Vivek R, Sri Neranjan R, Sarathraj A, Vivek R, Ashwath Mukunthan, Suresh C, Suryap Prakash L, Ashwath Mukunthan, Ajith Kumar, Abhinav M

CSG vs NRK – Venue and Timings

  • Venue – Indian Cement Company Ground, Tirunelveli.
  • Date & Time – June 23rd, 2022, 07:15 PM Indian Standard Time (IST)

CSG vs NRK match – Pitch Report

The best news for the batters is that the pitch for tomorrow’s game at the India Cements ground in Tirunelveli will have a level surface devoid of pace and bounce. However, because of the speedy outfield, a shot played at the ground will be simple to reach, making it once again appropriate for the batters.
From the bowling end, as previously mentioned, a lack of pace and bounce would not be advantageous to pacers or fast bowlers, however the surface might work wonders for spinners.

Weather Report

According to reports from weather.com, it is predicted to be partly overcast, 36 degrees Celsius, and up to 49% humidity throughout the match. Although it is less likely to rain when there is 10 percent of precipitation, it is still impossible to predict with precision because the monsoon season is still in full swing.

Match Prediction

This year Defending champions CSG has a strong batting line-up whereas from the NRK, and despite of their numerous looking option available in the team, they lack batting depth in their middle order. Whereas, the CSG appears to be more evenly balanced.

Final Prediction

The 3 time Tamil Nadu Premier League winners (2017, 2019 & 2021), have strong chances to win the first match against the Nellai Royal Kings
